Indicate which of the following is a linear combination of $A=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      3& 2\\
			0 & 1 
    \end{array}\right]$, $B=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      0& -1 \\
			1 & 2 
    \end{array}\right]$ and $C=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      5& 4 \\
			-1 & 0
    \end{array}\right]$.

Suppose that $$A=\left( 
 \begin{array}{rrr}
1 & 2  & -1  \\ 
0 & 0 & 2  \\ 
-1 & -2 & 3  \\ 
2 & 4 & 0 \end{array}
\right)$$ and $$B=\left( 
 \begin{array}{rrr}
0 & 1  & 1  \\ 
2 & 2 & 0  \\ 
0 & 3 & 2 \end{array}
\right).$$ Which of the following matrices has rank $3$?

